 The Oppositional Gaze # In our reading for this week, So Mayer asserts, &ldquo;What queer feminists do onscreen—and to the screen—is theory.&rdquo;
In what ways does The Watermelon Woman &ldquo;do theory&rdquo;? In particular, how does Cheryl Dunye use the film to theorize what bell hooks calls &ldquo;the oppositional gaze&rdquo;?
Zine contribution by Avrie #
